===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|month|lang=enm|sc=Latn}}, {{term|moneth|lang=enm|sc=Latn}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|monaþ|mōnað|month|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*mēnōþs||month}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*mḗh₁n̥s||moon, month}}, probably from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*mê-||to measure}}, referring to the moon's phases as the measure of time, equivalent to {{suffix|moon|th}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|moneth||month|lang=sco}}; {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|muunt||month|lang=frr}}; {{etyl|stq|-}} {{term|Mound||month|lang=stq}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|maand||month|lang=nl}}; {{etyl|nds-de|-}} {{term|Maand|lang=nds-de}}, {{term|Monat||month|lang=nds-de}}; {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Monat||month|lang=de}}; {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|måned||month|lang=da}}; {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|månad||month|lang=sv}}; {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|mánuði||month|lang=is}}; Ancient Greek {{term|μήν|tr=mḗn|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}; Armenian {{term|ամիս|tr=amis|lang=hy}}; Old Irish {{term|mí|lang=sga}}; {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|мѣсѧць|tr=měsęcĭ|lang=cu|sc=Cyrs}}. See also [[moon]].

